5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 608, L.D. 1493, “An Act to Eliminate
10 Tax and Wage Incentives for Visual Media Production Companies”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Limit Corporate Use of the Visual Media Production Credit'
13 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
14 following:
15 'Sec. 1. 5 MRSA §13090-L, sub-§2-A, ¶D, as enacted by PL 2009, c. 470, §1, is
16 amended by amending subparagraph (5) to read:
17 (5) A finished production that solicits funds; or
18 Sec. 2. 5 MRSA §13090-L, sub-§2-A, ¶D, as enacted by PL 2009, c. 470, §1, is
19 amended by amending subparagraph (6) to read:
20 (6) A production for which records are required to be maintained by 18 United
21 States Code, Section 2257.;
22 Sec. 3. 5 MRSA §13090-L, sub-§2-A, ¶D, as enacted by PL 2009, c. 470, §1, is
23 amended by enacting a new subparagraph (7) to read:
24 (7) A commercial or promotional production intended to advance a product or
25 service to the benefit of an individual or organization; or
26 Sec. 4. 5 MRSA §13090-L, sub-§2-A, ¶D, as enacted by PL 2009, c. 470, §1, is
27 amended by enacting a new subparagraph (8) to read:
28 (8) A production produced primarily for industrial, corporate or institutional
29 purposes or for internal use.'
30 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
31 number to read consecutively.
